  "prompt": "What on earth should I be instead of a fashionista if I'm an artist that draws?",
  "response": "If you\u2019re an artist who draws and you\u2019re looking for a term that aligns more closely with your artistic identity than \u201cfashionista,\u201d you might consider calling yourself an \"illustrator\" or \"visual artist.\" These terms emphasize your focus on creating art, whether it be through drawing, painting, digital art, or other mediums. You could also refer to yourself as a \"sketch artist\" if you focus mainly on drawing, or simply an \"artist\" if you engage in a broader range of creative activities. If your work has a specific style or focus, like \"concept artist\" or \"comic artist,\" those could be fitting as well. Ultimately, the choice depends on how you wish to define your artistry and share it with others.",
